I'd say something on the order of 90% of the land area of England have completely different accents which Americans never really get any exposure to I guess! In fact, because England has been sat here stewing and developing accents for an extra 1000+ years (without mass media or communication) over current American society, the density of different accents is kinda nuts; like I can comfortably tell the difference in accents between my town and other towns less than 20 miles away.
